      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bandits in the Global Shipping Lanes</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Kerry Tremain letter on Jack Hitt's August 20 article questions how piracy at sea relates to inequities of free-trade economy; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Jack Hitt's article (Aug. 20) is a heart thumper, a wonderfully written crime tale. But how piracy relates to ''the inequities of the free-trade economy'' is opaque at best.</p>
        <p>Kerry Tremain  Berkeley, Calif.</p>
      </block>
